                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                text="&lt;p>Dr. Darin J. Messina serves as Senior Vice President of Aesthetics R&amp;amp;D, leads the R&amp;amp;D organization responsible for the development of products in facial aesthetics (including neurotoxins &amp;amp; soft tissue fillers), body contouring, plastic surgery &amp;amp; regenerative medicine, and topical skincare.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>Dr. Messina joined Allergan in 2010 and has held positions of increasing responsibility developing medical devices and biologics. In his previous role at Allergan/AbbVie, Dr. Messina was Vice President, Head of Aesthetic Device R&amp;amp;D and had significant involvement in the acquisition and integration of Elastagen, LifeCell and Luminera, three companies with highly differentiated technology platforms.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>Prior to joining Allergan, Dr. Messina held roles at Johnson &amp;amp; Johnson, as part of Ethicon, Johnson &amp;amp; Johnson Internal Ventures, and Centocor. He has over 75 issued or pending patent applications related to stem cells, regenerative biomaterials, and aesthetic medicine.&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>Dr. Messina earned his Ph.D. in neuroscience from the University of Utah School of Medicine and undergraduate degrees from Northwestern University&lt;/p>&#xa;"
                                textIsRich="true"/>
